<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585536>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Turkonalassus mavi sp. n., habitus and details of structure: A—habitus dorsally, male; B—habitus dorsally, female; C—habitus ventrally, male; D—male inner sternite VIII; E—aedeagus (bml—baculi of median lobe, apa—apical piece apophises); F—spiculum gastrale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5585536/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585538>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Pseudevernia furfuraceae, host lichen (on Pinus nigra) of Turkonalassus mavi sp. n.: A—general view of tallus; B—damage of isidia from beetles (shown by arrows)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5585538/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

